dataCollection.message: To improve the search and browsing experience, Cliqz for Firefox sends data about web searches and website visits to Cliqz’s servers in a completely anonymous, privacy-safe way.

humanWeb3.message: Human Web collects Cliqz usage data in a completely anonymous, privacy-safe way.

humanWeb4.message: One for all. All for one. Together for a better web.

humanWeb5.message: By using Cliqz, you benefit from the wisdom of the crowd.  The community of users contributes – totally anonymously – to statistical web data. Our search technology uses this data to rate the relevance, trustworthiness and security of websites. We call this technology that indexes the Internet  with the help oft he users "Human Web".

humanWeb6.message: Cliqz's Human Web technology calculates web traffic statistics for websites that are visited by all users who participate in the Human Web, e.g. the sites’ addresses (URLs) and the amount of time people spend there. This is carried out entirely anonymously, without reference to any personal data or user identity. IP addresses are removed automatically from the Human Web data.

humanWeb7.message: Also completely anonymously, and separately from its web traffic data, Cliqz for Firefox records what the community of users search the web for and what they enter into the Cliqz universal browser bar (the combined search box and address bar at the top of your browser window). Each of such entries and site visits are evaluated only as a single event. We never combine data from multiple entries or multiple visits and do not attempt to draw even theoretically possible conclusions about our users. We also never associate any personal data (such as your IP or email address) with any events.

humanWeb8.message: Participating in Human Web is optional

humanWeb9.message: You can choose if you want Cliqz to submit anonymous statistical data to improve relevance and safety via the Human Web.

transparency_content.message: We respect your privacy and aim to protect it. Cliqz does not collect or store any personal data. Our Transparency Cockpit was built to give you insight into which data is generated when using the Cliqz browser. In real-time, it displays the data we receive when you start typing a search term into the address bar or when you visit a website. To protect your privacy, some data is blocked. I.e., these do not even leave your browser (e.g. geo-data, per your Cliqz settings).

transparency_search_content.message: The following are data signals concerning the Cliqz search function and display queries and URLs you enter or visit. They help us to optimize your search experience. As you can see, these data do not contain any personally identifiable information (“PII”). You are anonymous to Cliqz. You can route your searches through a network of proxy servers for an even stronger protection. Find more information here.

transparency_humanweb_content.message: Our Human Web technology uses statistical methods and algorithms to continuously enhance the quality of our search results. The collected anonymous, statistical data are related to queries and shown results displayed by one of the complementary search engines. The chosen data architecture prevents any inference about a natural person. The transfer of Human Web data is encrypted and routed through a network of proxy servers. Find more information here.

transparency_telemetry_content.message: Telemetry includes all data concerning the usage and performance of the browser and its features. We use these data to continuously improve your Cliqz experience. These data include e.g. the version number of the browser, or the time it takes to display Cliqz search results. Telemetry data do not contain any information about queries, search results or visited URLs. Find more information here.
